beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Discovered this gem at a Milwaukee Bucks game. Not usually much of a red fan, but this one hit the spot. Opened the world of Leinenkugal to me.
The only reason this exists is to let poor people get drunk. Not many beer-like qualities present.
A conglomerate can get it right with a mass produced beer. Looks good, tastes good, and you cant beat the price.
12 oz. bottle in Milwaukee. Very disapointed. Had heard so many good things. The flavor was all over the place.
16 oz, plastic bottle. Great ad campaigns dont make up for a products shortcomings, and this one has lots of them. Bad beer.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Bottle. Surprising how easily this dark beer goes down so smooth. Slight bitterness surrounded with a nice body. Leinies finest.
If Bud Light and Natural Light spawned this would be their bastard child. How can a company spend so much on advertising for junk?
Easily the most widely available beer. #1 in America for a reason. Highly accesilble and not many actual beer-like qualities present.
Bottled piss taste in a can. Reminds me of my early college years. Cheap. Will not go back down this path even for nostalgias sake.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Poured with a fair to diminishing head. Flavor was bitter up front with a nice finish. Will try again.
